==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Honorableness
<hw>Hon"or*a*ble*ness</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The state of
being honorable; eminence; distinction.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Conformity to the principles of honor, probity, or
moral rectitude; fairness; uprightness; reputableness.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Honorably</ent>⟦br⟧
